video.title: The Flash
video.synopsis: A forensics expert who wakes from a coma with amazing new powers squares off against forces threatening the city in this live-action superhero romp.

episodes.synopsis: Waking from a coma, Barry harnesses his newfound extraordinary speed to combat another metahuman who uses his power over the weather to loot banks.
episodes.title: Pilot

episodes.synopsis: Barry takes on multiple gunmen who storm an awards ceremony he's attending with Iris, but side effects from his new superpower catch up to him.
episodes.title: Fastest Man Alive

episodes.synopsis: The Flash and Joe track a deadly metahuman whose specialty is poisonous gases, and Caitlin relives the night of the explosion that killed her fiancé.
episodes.title: Things You Can't Outrun

episodes.synopsis: To steal a priceless diamond, Captain Cold acquires a specialized gun that can slay the Flash. Meanwhile, Joe disapproves of Iris and Eddie dating.
episodes.title: Going Rogue

episodes.synopsis: While he tries to persuade Iris to stop blogging about the Flash, Barry investigates an army general's connection to a metahuman with explosive power.
episodes.title: Plastique

episodes.synopsis: Barry takes on his former childhood bully, who can now turn himself into steel. In her blog, Iris finally coins the moniker "the Flash."
episodes.title: The Flash Is Born

episodes.synopsis: Using his metahuman power to siphon electricity, Blackout robs Barry of his speed, then sets his vindictive sights on S.T.A.R. Labs and Dr. Wells.
episodes.title: Power Outage

episodes.synopsis: The Arrow arrives to help the Flash investigate a lethal boomerang, but a metahuman who can control emotions turns the Flash against his former pal.
episodes.title: Flash vs. Arrow

episodes.synopsis: The Flash finally gets a chance to confront the Reverse-Flash, the man who killed his mother. Caitlin gets surprising news about her fiancé, Ronnie.
episodes.title: The Man in the Yellow Suit

episodes.synopsis: While the Flash prepares to vanquish the Reverse-Flash, Captain Cold and Heat Wave team up to kidnap Caitlin and lure the Flash to his doom.
episodes.title: Revenge of the Rogues

episodes.synopsis: An embittered former protégé of Dr. Wells uses sound waves to attack the Flash. Meanwhile, Iris faces trouble in her new job as a reporter.
episodes.title: The Sound and the Fury

episodes.synopsis: The Flash takes on a teleporting metahuman, Cisco investigates Ronnie's fate, and Barry and Caitlin go looking for love at a karaoke bar.
episodes.title: Crazy for You

episodes.synopsis: The Flash hunts for a dangerously transformed Ronnie after he attacks a scientist, and Joe and Cisco reinvestigate Nora Allen's murder.
episodes.title: The Nuclear Man

episodes.synopsis: Gen. Eiling attempts to use Ronnie and Dr. Stein for his supersoldier project, and Barry confronts the possibility that he has traveled through time.
episodes.title: Fallout

episodes.synopsis: A metahuman who can control the weather targets Joe to avenge the death of his brother. Cisco learns the truth about the Reverse-Flash.
episodes.title: Out of Time

episodes.synopsis: The Flash travels back in time to prevent a catastrophic tidal wave, but the time warp sparks another attack from Captain Cold and Heat Wave.
episodes.title: Rogue Time

episodes.synopsis: The Flash pursues the Trickster and the copycat villain who broke him out of jail. Barry discovers the truth about Dr. Wells.
episodes.title: Tricksters

episodes.synopsis: Felicity Smoak and the Atom team up with the Flash to take on a metahuman who's using swarms of robotic bees to attack scientists.
episodes.title: All Star Team Up

episodes.synopsis: While Joe and Cisco intensify their investigation into Dr. Wells, the Flash faces Everyman, a metahuman who can morph into any person he touches.
episodes.title: Who Is Harrison Wells?

episodes.synopsis: After Barry glimpses the future, he and the others risk Cisco's safety in order to trick Dr. Wells into a confession.
episodes.title: The Trap

episodes.synopsis: After the powerfully telepathic gorilla Grodd forces Gen. Eiling to commit a robbery, the Flash and his team enter the city sewers to stop the beast.
episodes.title: Grodd Lives

episodes.synopsis: When he learns that Dr. Wells has reactivated the particle accelerator, the Flash asks Captain Cold for help saving the metahumans trapped inside it.
episodes.title: Rogue Air

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Wells offers Barry a tempting proposition: a chance to go back in time to save his mother. But the consequences could be catastrophic.
episodes.title: Fast Enough

episodes.synopsis: Six months after facing the singularity, Team Flash has split up, leaving Barry alone at S.T.A.R. Labs and in his fight against metahumans.
episodes.title: The Man Who Saved Central City

episodes.synopsis: Jay Garrick, a speedster from Earth-2, warns the team about an evil speedster named Zoom. Cisco has more visions, one of which leads to Sand Demon.
episodes.title: Flash of Two Worlds

episodes.synopsis: Iris takes risks to get her story, and Joe is forced to tell her a long-held secret. Captain Cold is back -- but this time he needs the Flash's help.
episodes.title: Family of Rogues

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Stein needs a stabilizing force to keep from exploding, and the team finds two potential matches. Patty and Barry track down a man-shark.
episodes.title: The Fury of Firestorm

episodes.synopsis: A peek at Earth-2 reveals tension between Jay and Dr. Wells. The latest metahuman stalking the Flash, Dr. Light, resembles a woman from Barry's past.
episodes.title: The Darkness and the Light

episodes.synopsis: The team recruits an unlikely ally for its plan to capture Zoom. Cisco tries using his newfound powers on Earth-2. Dr. Wells, Barry and Zoom face off.
episodes.title: Enter Zoom

episodes.synopsis: Barry's confidence is shaken, and Earth-2 Dr. Wells must step in to rescue Caitlin from Grodd, a superintelligent gorilla who feels angry and alone.
episodes.title: Gorilla Warfare

episodes.synopsis: Vandal Savage poses a new threat to Central City -- he's dangerous and powerful, but not a metahuman. Barry turns to the Arrow for help.
episodes.title: Legends of Today

episodes.synopsis: Zoom offers Dr. Wells a deal he can't refuse. The Trickster delivers a Christmas surprise, leaving Barry with a hard choice. Iris tells Joe the truth.
episodes.title: Running to Stand Still

episodes.synopsis: Barry and Patty's special night out is interrupted by an attack by the Turtle. Jay reveals he's ill. Joe and Wally try being father and son.
episodes.title: Potential Energy

episodes.synopsis: The Reverse-Flash kidnaps Dr. McGee in an attempt to return to his own time. Cisco finds the key to tapping his powers. The timeline ruptures.
episodes.title: The Reverse-Flash Returns

episodes.synopsis: Barry is losing speed, but can't pinpoint why. Iris plots to keep Wally safe from drag racing, and they both end up in the way of Tar Pit's revenge.
episodes.title: Fast Lane

episodes.synopsis: In a bold plan, the team heads to Earth-2 after sealing the breaches. Barry steps into his doppelgänger's life and gets distracted from the mission.
episodes.title: Welcome to Earth-2

episodes.synopsis: Geomancer wreaks havoc on Earth-1. Iris's editor raises doubts about the Flash's heroism. In Zoom's lair, the Man in the Iron Mask taps out a message.
episodes.title: Escape From Earth-2

episodes.synopsis: King Shark is on the loose and determined to kill the Flash. Barry and Wally have trouble seeing eye to eye. Zoom's true identity is revealed.
episodes.title: King Shark

episodes.synopsis: A new speedster named Trajectory appears and is able to outrun Barry. She breaks into S.T.A.R. Labs looking for even more power, at any cost.
episodes.title: Trajectory

episodes.synopsis: Barry gets a lesson in how time travel works -- and the new dangers it holds -- when he runs into the past to find out how to get faster.
episodes.title: Flash Back

episodes.synopsis: The team pieces together Zoom's origin story and uses it to concoct a trap. But when Wally ends up in danger, Barry is forced to make a sacrifice.
episodes.title: Versus Zoom

episodes.synopsis: A metahuman with super strength comes to Dr. Wells looking for a cure. Caitlin and Killer Frost swap life stories while imprisoned in Zoom's lair.
episodes.title: Back to Normal

episodes.synopsis: The team uses its scientific skills to cover up for Barry's missing powers. Zoom and Caitlin return to Earth-1. Barry faces a risky decision.
episodes.title: Rupture

episodes.synopsis: Barry takes a journey through the speed force, revisiting important moments and people in his life. Re-creating the accident has an unexpected effect.
episodes.title: The Runaway Dinosaur

episodes.synopsis: Zoom and his new pack of metahumans are ravaging Earth-1. Barry feels unstoppable, but Zoom is intent on proving that they are more alike than not.
episodes.title: Invincible

episodes.synopsis: Zoom challenges Barry to a race, but the team suspects a trap and tries to talk Barry out of it. Only one speedster will survive the epic final fight.
episodes.title: The Race of His Life

episodes.synopsis: After altering the past, Barry sees his new life hit a snag as he begins to lose his memories. Central City gains a new speedster.
episodes.title: Flashpoint

episodes.synopsis: Barry learns some cold, hard facts about the nature of resetting timelines. A newly superpowered Clariss leads the team to an even greater enemy.
episodes.title: Paradox

episodes.synopsis: Abused foster child Frankie Kane unleashes an alternate personality armed with immense magnetic powers. Harry seeks advice for Jesse from Earth-1.
episodes.title: Magenta

episodes.synopsis: Two unhinged former associates of Leonard Snart escape from a mirror-like dimension to take aim at Central City. Barry continues to train Jesse.
episodes.title: The New Rogues

episodes.synopsis: Team Flash must deal with a giant creature that seems to appear and reappear with ease. Hoping to find answers, Caitlin secretly visits her mother.
episodes.title: Monster

episodes.synopsis: After sending a shadowy metahuman to keep the Flash occupied, Alchemy attempts to recruit Wally by offering him the superpowers from his dreams.
episodes.title: Shade

episodes.synopsis: Barry vows to take down the self-proclaimed speed god Savitar while Joe aims to save Wally. Caitlin finds herself overwhelmed by her evil side.
episodes.title: Killer Frost

episodes.synopsis: When an iron-fisted alien species threatens all metahumans, Barry assembles Supergirl, Team Arrow and the Legends for an all-out battle.
episodes.title: Invasion!

episodes.synopsis: Barry asks Earth-3’s Jay Garrick for help in the fight against Savitar. The heroes see a potential opportunity after learning Alchemy's identity.
episodes.title: The Present

episodes.synopsis: Visions of the future give Barry pause about Wally's efforts as Kid Flash. H.R. opens the museum. Caitlin approaches Julian with a special request.
episodes.title: Borrowing Problems From the Future

episodes.synopsis: Cisco faces a fight to the death after challenging an Earth-19 bounty hunter gunning for H.R. Iris convinces Wally to help her bust an arms dealer.
episodes.title: Dead or Alive

episodes.synopsis: Team Flash has its hands full when a metahuman with a withering touch starts killing off the counterparts of the cops who arrested him in Flashpoint.
episodes.title: Untouchable

episodes.synopsis: While Wally and Jesse fend off criminals in Central City, the rest of the team attempts to rescue Harry from Grodd in Gorilla City.
episodes.title: Attack on Gorilla City

episodes.synopsis: Grodd and his forces plot a massive attack on Central City. Barry begins to think killing the gorilla may be his only option.
episodes.title: Attack on Central City

episodes.synopsis: Wally consults with the team after visions of Savitar turn dangerously physical. An unexpected visitor soon leaves him even more disoriented.
episodes.title: The Wrath of Savitar

episodes.synopsis: A desperate Barry encounters fallen foes and allies after entering the speed force to save Wally. Jesse decides to face Savitar herself.
episodes.title: Into the Speed Force

episodes.synopsis: After Music Meister puts them both in comas, Barry and Kara find themselves trapped and forced to participate in a dreamy musical.
episodes.title: Duet

episodes.synopsis: Gypsy pursues a 64th-century criminal who arrives in Central City and offers Team Flash valuable information in exchange for his freedom.
episodes.title: Abra Kadabra

episodes.synopsis: While most of the team remains in 2017 to search for Killer Frost, Barry travels years into the future in hopes of learning Savitar's identity.
episodes.title: The Once and Future Flash

episodes.synopsis: Barry, Cisco and H.R. must subdue an increasingly aggressive Killer Frost as they seek out the woman destined to thwart Savitar.
episodes.title: I Know Who You Are

episodes.synopsis: H.R. and Tracy scramble to design the speed force trap. The truth about Savitar's origins inspires Cisco and Julian to attempt a risky solution.
episodes.title: Cause and Effect

episodes.synopsis: While Team Flash locates the only energy source capable of powering the bazooka, Barry visits 1892 to recruit an unlikely ally skilled in thievery.
episodes.title: Infantino Street

episodes.synopsis: After Savitar initiates a desperate plan to disperse himself throughout time, Barry realizes his best bet is to face the godlike time remnant head-on.
episodes.title: Finish Line

episodes.synopsis: As Barry remains trapped in the speed force, a powerful new villain issues a deadly ultimatum, putting Iris and company in a tough spot.
episodes.title: The Flash Reborn

episodes.synopsis: While struggling to adjust to Cisco's upgraded suit, Barry takes on a dangerous meta who has the power to control technology.
episodes.title: Mixed Signals

episodes.synopsis: When Barry and company are hit by a flurry of accidents and problems, they realize there may be more to their poor fortune than simple bad luck.
episodes.title: Luck Be a Lady

episodes.synopsis: Cisco is shocked to see Gypsy and her father, Breacher, on Earth-1. Meanwhile, Barry clashes with an old foe, the slippery Ralph Dibny.
episodes.title: Elongated Journey into Night

episodes.synopsis: Barry and the boys hit the town for a bachelor party while Iris enjoys a night out with the girls. But the celebrations hit a few snags along the way.
episodes.title: Girl's Night Out

episodes.synopsis: Ralph Dibny dons Cisco's customized super-suit and tries life out as Elongated Man. Meanwhile, a foe targets collectors of Native American artifacts.
episodes.title: When Harry Met Harry...

episodes.synopsis: Barry's suspicions about DeVoe's identity and intentions cause a rift with the rest of the team. Iris prepares for the big wedding.
episodes.title: Therefore I Am

episodes.synopsis: Barry teams up with Supergirl, Green Arrow and the Legends of Tomorrow to fight an insidious invasion from Earth-X.
episodes.title: Crisis on Earth-X, Part 3

episodes.synopsis: With Barry trapped in a speedster-proof prison and Amunet holding Caitlin hostage, the strapped team faces a difficult choice about who to save.
episodes.title: Don't Run

episodes.synopsis: Framed and on trial for a crime he didn't commit, Barry must decide if now's the time to reveal his alter ego to the world.
episodes.title: The Trial of the Flash

episodes.synopsis: A devious foe returns to Central City and puts Ralph's heroism to the test. Meanwhile, Barry strives to stay positive despite dire circumstances.
episodes.title: The Elongated Knight Rises

episodes.synopsis: Sylbert Rundine can shrink anything he touches -- a fact that Cisco and Ralph learn firsthand while battling the metahuman.
episodes.title: Honey, I Shrunk Team Flash

episodes.synopsis: When Barry gets ominous news about Amunet's plans, he must make a dangerous choice in order to save his cellmates.
episodes.title: True Colors

episodes.synopsis: Barry and the team meet an unusual ally whose musical talents tend to leave folks floored. Meanwhile, Ralph reevaluates his priorities.
episodes.title: Subject 9

episodes.synopsis: Barry slows time to a crawl while desperately searching for a way to stop an already-exploding bomb from destroying Central City.
episodes.title: Enter Flashtime

episodes.synopsis: After a run-in with a sinister new foe, Iris acquires all of Barry's speed and steps into a new role as the hero who must protect Central City.
episodes.title: Run Iris, Run

episodes.synopsis: Ralph's devil-may-care approach to tracking the remaining bus metas tests Barry's patience. Cisco fields Breacher's request for a favor.
episodes.title: Null and Annoyed

episodes.synopsis: As Team Flash prepares to face off against The Thinker, Ralph weighs taking a risky step. Also, Harry's behavior raises red flags with Joe.
episodes.title: Lose Yourself

episodes.synopsis: Needing a little help to safely move an explosive meta, Barry and Team Flash call on Leo Snart -- aka Citizen Cold -- for a hand.
episodes.title: Fury Rogue

episodes.synopsis: Gypsy joins Barry and Team Flash in a desperate attempt to stop the Thinker's plan from coming to fruition.
episodes.title: Therefore She Is

episodes.synopsis: Barry and Team Flash strike an ill-advised deal with an unlikely partner. Meanwhile, Cisco councils Harry following some rough news.
episodes.title: Harry and the Harrisons

episodes.synopsis: As DeVoe's endgame draws near, Barry faces a gut-wrenching decision: go to battle solo or enlist his friends -- and possibly risk their lives.
episodes.title: Think Fast

episodes.synopsis: Barry makes a daring attempt to enter Devoe's consciousness. Meanwhile, a suprising ally gives Team Flash a much-needed hand.
episodes.title: We Are the Flash

episodes.synopsis: While Team Flash takes on a sinister meta, Barry and Iris struggle to make sense of their guest from an altogether different era.
episodes.title: Nora

episodes.synopsis: Barry teaches Nora the finer points of being a speedster. The members of Team Flash discover their newest enemy wants what they want.
episodes.title: Blocked

episodes.synopsis: As Caitlin searches for answers about her mysterious past, the members of Team Flash put their heads together in hopes of stopping Cicada's savagery.
episodes.title: The Death of Vibe

episodes.synopsis: Nora catches the attention of an ambitious -- and dangerous -- millennial armed with meta tech. Meanwhile, Ralph needs an ego boost.
episodes.title: News Flash

episodes.synopsis: A dangerous and disturbing new meta gets the drop on Barry. Meanwhile, Iris learns a distressing fact about the future.
episodes.title: All Doll'd Up

episodes.synopsis: Eager to reconnect with her father, Caitlin struggles to heed the concerns of her friends. Also, Iris and Sherloque investigate a clue about Cicada.
episodes.title: The Icicle Cometh

episodes.synopsis: Team Flash braces for a stormy run-in with the powerful Weather Witch. Meanwhile, Nora struggles to come to terms with her father's disappearance.
episodes.title: O Come,	 All Ye Thankful

episodes.synopsis: To stop Cicada, Barry and his daughter must first travel back in time. But is Barry ready to share his past with Nora?
episodes.title: What's Past Is Prologue

episodes.synopsis: Oliver Queen -- aka Arrow -- wakes to discover he's switched bodies with Barry Allen. Convincing Team Flash won't be easy.
episodes.title: Elseworlds: Hour One

episodes.synopsis: As Nora struggles with a troubling revelation, Team Flash takes on a daunting duo. Also, Caitlin and Cisco discuss a possible meta-human cure.
episodes.title: The	Flash & The Furious

episodes.synopsis: Nora's speed healing stops working, putting her in grave danger. Barry is fueled by an unfamiliar rage. Caitlin's work on a cure faces interference.
episodes.title: Seeing Red

episodes.synopsis: Desperate to keep her parents from learning her secrets, Nora takes a drastic -- perhaps fatal -- step. Meanwhile, Ralph takes Cisco out on the town.
episodes.title: Memorabilia

episodes.synopsis: In hopes of taking down Cicada, Barry and Ralph go undercover in the criminal underworld and find their integrity tested.
episodes.title: Goldfaced

episodes.synopsis: Nora races to save her mother from serious danger while Barry works to finalize the metahuman cure. Also, Cisco hits the town with Kamilla.
episodes.title: Cause and XS

episodes.synopsis: When Gorilla Grodd launches an attack on Central City, Barry and Team Flash must fight alongside an unexpected ally.
episodes.title: King Shark Vs Gorilla Grodd

episodes.synopsis: Barry and Team Flash search for a way to force Cicada into taking the meta-human cure. Also, Joe gets back to work.
episodes.title: Failure is an Orphan

episodes.synopsis: Barry and Team Flash cross paths with a woman harboring a deep secret from her family. Nora considers revealing the truth about her work with Thawne.
episodes.title: Time Bomb

episodes.synopsis: Barry and Iris butt heads over how to deal with their daughter's shocking partnership. Also, Team Flash searches Nora's journal for answers.
episodes.title: Godspeed

episodes.synopsis: After Barry makes a big familial decision without her input, Iris elects to go solo. Also, Caitlin and her mother must unite against a frosty foe.
episodes.title: Snow Pack

episodes.synopsis: As a trio of villains unleashes havoc in Central City, Barry struggles to come to terms with his daughter's deception.
episodes.title: Gone Rogue

episodes.synopsis: When they learn of Cicada II's threat to release a disastrous virus, Barry and Team Flash must prepare for the worst.
episodes.title: The Girl With The Red Lightning

episodes.synopsis: Team Flash sets out to destroy Cicada's dagger once and for all. Also, Cisco opens up to Kamilla and Nora struggles to forgive herself.
episodes.title: Legacy

episodes.synopsis: Still grieving, Barry distracts himself with a black hole problem while Iris searches for an eccentric scientist who may have some answers.
episodes.title: Into The Void

episodes.synopsis: At Iris's urging, Barry travels into the future for a second opinion about his fate. Meanwhile, the rest of Team Flash sets out to help a meta.
episodes.title: A Flash of The Lightning

episodes.synopsis: As Barry secretly prepares for a seemingly unavoidable fate, he and Team Flash track a metahuman who's collecting dark matter by any means necessary.
episodes.title: Dead Man Running

episodes.synopsis: As the Crisis draws closer, Barry tries to prepare Cisco for the inevitable. Also, Ramsey Rosso searches for a more permanent cure to his illness.
episodes.title: There Will Be Blood

episodes.synopsis: Cisco puts his leadership skills to the test while Barry and Iris take a mini-vacation. Meanwhile, Killer Frost sets out to track down Ramsey Rosso.
episodes.title: Kiss Kiss Breach Breach

episodes.synopsis: Barry tags along with Ralph in hopes of teaching him to be heroic in a post-Flash world. Nash asks Allegra for help with a life-or-death project.
episodes.title: License To Elongate

episodes.synopsis: Barry is tested as never before when Ramsey Rosso infects him with a malicious virus. Iris investigates a sinister plot.
episodes.title: The Last Temptation of Barry Allen: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: As Iris and Cisco fight to save Barry from Ramsey’s evil influence, the rest of Team Flash battles Bloodwork’s army throughout Central City.
episodes.title: The Last Temptation of Barry Allen: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Joined by Supergirl, Black Lightning and others, Barry and Team Flash search for a way to stop the antimatter wave from destroying the multiverse.
episodes.title: Crisis on Infinite Earths: Hour Three

episodes.synopsis: Following a hot tip, Iris investigates a nefarious organization. Meanwhile, Barry sets out to uncover the mystery behind a mask.
episodes.title: Marathon

episodes.synopsis: Barry and Iris's Valentine's Day dinner is rudely interrupted by a pesky nemesis. Also, Allegra gets some unsolicited assistance from Frost.
episodes.title: Love is a Battlefield

episodes.synopsis: Months after his search went cold, Ralph finally gets a lead on Sue Dearbon. Meanwhile, Iris plays with mirrors and Barry re-opens a closed case.
episodes.title: A Girl Named Sue

episodes.synopsis: Frustrated and overwhelmed by all the lingering changes from the Crisis, Barry undertakes an experiment with surprising consequences.
episodes.title: Grodd Friended Me

episodes.synopsis: Kid Flash delivers a dire warning about the Speed Force to Barry. Also, Cisco returns to help take on a dangerous meta.
episodes.title: Death of the Speed Force

episodes.synopsis: Eva enlists the duplicate versions of Iris and Kamilla for a mission. Plus, Team Flash examines Nash while Barry faces a dangerous new foe.
episodes.title: The Exorcism of Nash Wells

episodes.synopsis: Despite being in serious danger, Joe refuses to take caution. Barry struggles to conserve his speed. Iris shares a secret with Eva.
episodes.title: So Long and Goodnight

episodes.synopsis: Increasingly worried about his wife's shifting personality, Barry searches for an explanation. Also, Eva prepares to step into a new world.
episodes.title: Liberation

episodes.synopsis: The return of Godspeed inspires Barry to ask Hartley Rathaway for help, as tension and doubt threaten to tear Team Flash apart.
episodes.title: Pay the Piper

episodes.synopsis: Barry and Ralph investigate a suspicious warehouse in hopes of finally getting a lead on Eva. Later, Barry delivers Carver a dire warning.
episodes.title: Success is Assured

episodes.synopsis: Barry's speed drops dangerously low, pushing Team Flash to search for a solution that may require a terrible sacrifice.
episodes.title: All's Wells That Ends Wells

episodes.synopsis: Barry gains the power to speed think, but his new ability isn't without its downsides. Also, Eva faces a devastating truth.
episodes.title: The Speed of Thought

episodes.synopsis: Team Flash finds itself at a loss as Eva's powers grow frighteningly strong. An ally with a familiar face shares an urgent piece of advice.
episodes.title: Mother

episodes.synopsis: As Team Flash helps Central City to rebuild, another villain puts his cards on the table. Also, Barry and Iris struggle to return to normalcy.
episodes.title: Central City Strong

episodes.synopsis: A new enemy turns the team's darkest fears into terrifying hallucinations. Also, Killer Frost and Caitlin Snow get a little time to themselves.
episodes.title: Fear Me

episodes.synopsis: Chester and Cisco become trapped in 1998, reliving one of Chester’s worst days. As Barry recovers, Iris and the Speed Force form a connection.
episodes.title: The One with the Nineties

episodes.synopsis: Frost is framed for a brutal attack. Meanwhile, Chester gets his first crime scene job and Barry and Iris deal with a houseguest.
episodes.title: Growing Pains

episodes.synopsis: Facing the fight of her life, Frost is determined to do things her way. Meanwhile, Barry and Nora investigate a possible new metahuman.
episodes.title: The People vs. Killer Frost

episodes.synopsis: In the wake of a painful betrayal, Barry seeks an old friend's help for a time-sensitive mission. Also, Iris, Allegra and Kamilla chase down a lead.
episodes.title: Timeless

episodes.synopsis: Iris searches for the truth about Psych's motivations. Barry offers to train Alexa in hopes of fending off a looming threat. Cisco ponders a move.
episodes.title: Family Matters: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Barry and Iris vow to hide Bashir and Alexa from a vengeance-fueled Nora. Meanwhile, a massive storm threatens to destroy Central City.
episodes.title: Family Matters: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Cisco and Kamila share some huge news with the team — so why does nobody seem to care? Also, a new meta makes victims temporarily euphoric.
episodes.title: Good-Bye Vibrations

episodes.synopsis: Cecile struggles to escape a psychic prison. Chester takes over for Cisco, but it's a rocky transition. Also, Team Flash plans a heist.
episodes.title: Masquerade

episodes.synopsis: As Allegra attempts to reform her dangerous cousin, Barry and Iris take some time away from work. Also, Joe digs into Kristen Kramer's past.
episodes.title: Rayo De Luz

episodes.synopsis: Just as Barry thinks he has cause to celebrate, a gang of Godspeeds attacks. Caitlin examines Ultraviolet while Frost wavers on trusting Chillblaine.
episodes.title: Enemy at the Gates

episodes.synopsis: As Barry worries the Godspeed civil war might harm his family, Team Flash receives some welcome help. Joe and Kramer confront her former friend, Creyke.
episodes.title: P.O.W.

episodes.synopsis: Barry and Iris's future children, XS and Bart, make an appearance. Meanwhile, the Godspeed war grows deadlier and Allegra keeps a problem to herself.
episodes.title: Heart of the Matter: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: In a desperate attempt to defeat Godspeed and put an end to the speedster war, Barry calls upon his friends and family to join the fight.
episodes.title: Heart of the Matter: Part 2
